{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Design System First, Pages Second\n      Build a complete, documented component library first (Phase 1). Then rebuild every page using only those components (Phase 2).\n      \n        \n          Strengths\n          \n            Highly systematic — every component documented\n            Future-proof — new pages auto-inherit system\n            Enforced consistency — no one-off styles possible\n            Great for onboarding new developers\n          \n        \n        \n          Weaknesses\n          \n            Slower visible results — Phase 1 has no user-facing changes\n            Inconsistency persists during Phase 1\n            Over-engineering risk\n            More total effort (documentation + components + migration)\n          \n        \n      \n      \n        Best for: Teams growing in size who need a shared design language and are OK with delayed user-facing impact.","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775322833227}
