{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Component-Layer Rewrite Recommended\n      Replace the styling layer across all pages in one coordinated push. Remove Bootstrap, consolidate CSS, reskin everything using the existing UI components.\n      \n        \n          Strengths\n          \n            Eliminates Bootstrap/Tailwind conflict permanently\n            Every page gets touched = guaranteed consistency\n            Minimal risk to business logic\n            One coordinated push = no jarring transitions\n          \n        \n        \n          Weaknesses\n          \n            Large diff (~60-80 files)\n            Needs thorough QA across all roles\n            No living style guide documentation\n          \n        \n      \n      \n        Best for: Teams that want immediate, full consistency and can dedicate a focused sprint to the overhaul.","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775322836526}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Page-by-Page Visual Overhaul\n      Redesign each page individually, starting with Login → Dashboard → Requests → everything else. Ship improvements incrementally.\n      \n        \n          Strengths\n          \n            Fastest first visual win (Login in Sprint 1)\n            Incremental — each sprint ships something polished\n            Easy to pause at any point\n            Lower risk per individual sprint\n          \n        \n        \n          Weaknesses\n          \n            Jarring transitions between new and old pages\n            Style drift across sprints\n            Bootstrap stays until every page is converted\n            Cleanup pass usually needed at the end\n            More total work overall\n          \n        \n      \n      \n        Best for: Teams that can't dedicate a full sprint to UI work and need to ship incrementally between feature work.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1775322840510}
